## What works (verified)

- **Canonical-skill, no duplication:** `copy_skill_into_workspace` (`scripts/okr-runner.py:1039-1046`) injects the single `skills/reverse-tornado-okr` into the disposable workspace unconditionally, independent of `inject_skill_context`; `AGENTS.md:7` and `README.md` point edits at the canonical path. The dogfood test correctly relies on project rules (not prompt injection) to discover it (`inject_skill_context: false`).
- **Validation runs both new checkers:** `validate-skills.sh` → `okr-runner.py validate` calibrates `okra_terminal_memory` (golden pass/fail) and `okra_terminal_run_store` (self-built temp stores; golden README placeholder satisfies the existence check) at `:766-790`. Case schema validation now type-checks the two new booleans (`:512-514`) and the two new check types are allow-listed (`:503-504`).
- **Isolated evals + raw artifact preservation:** the new case is auto-discovered by `load_cases`, included in the default `--agent both` run, and documented in `AGENTS.md:76` / `README.md`. The deterministic hash-chain verification in `load_log` (`okra_terminal_run_store.py:119-151`) is a genuinely strong anti-false-confidence gate (seq/prev_hash/payload_sha256/record_hash all recomputed); the committed dogfood ledger and `status.md` last-hash actually agree (`…/status.md:7` ↔ `…/ledger.jsonl:4`).
- **`single_llm_truth` enforcement and honest blocked-state handling:** the deterministic `single_llm_truth_acceptance_count == 0` read is enforced structurally (`okra_terminal_run_store.py:316-320`) and the review-gap/blocked path is modeled and calibrated (`:229-242`, `:684-719`). The real dogfood run honestly recorded a `cannot` flag when independent review tooling failed rather than claiming a clean done (`…/run-terminal.v1.json:33-37`) — the intended behavior.

**Net:** the harness wiring (skill location, validation, eval dispatch, deterministic gates, opt-in project-rule honoring) is sound and a future Claude/Codex agent can operate it. The real problem is in the *committed evidence*: `.okra/` is now durable, tracked memory, but its terminalized run stores would fail the very `okra_terminal_run_store` gate the change introduces (Findings 1–2). I did not modify any files.
